      "writtenOn": "2020-01-03T18:56:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I assume uploading is the time consuming operation (compare to streaming query test results), so I chose a number to parallel the uploading the most (according to https://osscs.corp.google.com/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/common/bq/eventupload.go): \n8000 \u003d 500 (default batch size) * 16 (workPool size)\n\nWDYT?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 38,
        "startChar": 26,
        "endLine": 38,
        "endChar": 30
      },
      "revId": "12ef22db34db6c8e931b78305d6fab5416733afd",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d4cf231e_6842a2c7",
        "filename": "resultdb/cmd/backend/bigquery_export.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 38,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-01-03T19:31:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "the fact that we have to do this math seems to be a signal that Uploader is in the way. I never thought that Uploader is a good abstraction. The most valuable part of the bq package is message-\u003ebigquery.Row conversion.\n\ni think it would be simpler if we simply didn\u0027t use the Uploader. Instead use bigquery.Uploader.Put and split by 500 rows-per-batch. Then you don\u0027t have to think about this.\n\nAlso it would be more concurrent. Right now we fetch 8k rows first, and only then start uploading. If we batch and upload ourselves, then as soon as we get first 500 rows, we start uploading.",
      "parentUuid": "af94452e_eca8249b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 38,
        "startChar": 26,
        "endLine": 38,
        "endChar": 30
      },
      "revId": "12ef22db34db6c8e931b78305d6fab5416733afd",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b462dcf2_36626847",
        "filename": "resultdb/cmd/backend/bigquery_export.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 38,
      "author": {
        "id": 1157909
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-01-05T04:33:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "As I mentioned in my previous comment, I assume uploading is slower than streaming, so if we make the batch size to be 500, the result channel could be filled up quickly and blocked by uploading. If so we may need uploading in parallel, which we can get for free from the Uploader. If waiting 8000 rows is not necessary, we can easily change the maxRowsInBatch, say, 1000?\n\nStepping back, we can achieve the same goal (even if continue using the Uploader) by reducing maxRowsInBatch to 500, right?",
      "parentUuid": "d4cf231e_6842a2c7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 38,
        "startChar": 26,
        "endLine": 38,
        "endChar": 30
      },
      "revId": "12ef22db34db6c8e931b78305d6fab5416733afd",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a7624976_87553a64",
        "filename": "resultdb/cmd/backend/bigquery_export.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 38,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-01-06T16:38:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e blocked by uploading\nuploading must not block streaming. it should happen in a separate goroutine. it would consume a channel of batches, not a channel of individual rows.\n\nyes, we can achieve improved concurrency by using 500 batch Size, but this also means that we are assuming a specific behavior in the bigquery library. Also I still don\u0027t see what value does bigquery.Uploader provide.\n\nalso, looks like the use of bigquery.Uploader actually adds a problem: it generates random insertIDs\nhttps://source.chromium.org/chromium/_/chromium/infra/luci/luci-go/+/270a41695194988c426bfd07f53923564bdd8f0f:common/bq/eventupload.go;l\u003d398;drc\u003de94f964255cda28b1702217c7d2e6925870444de\nbut we want to use test result names to avoid insertion of test results twice (in case of a retry of the invocation task), so I think bigquery.Uploader adds more harm than value",
      "parentUuid": "b462dcf2_36626847",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 38,
        "startChar": 26,
        "endLine": 38,
        "endChar": 30
      },
      "revId": "12ef22db34db6c8e931b78305d6fab5416733afd",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
